The paper proposes a novel method for saliency detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of CNNs for both pixel-level and region-level saliency estimation suggests that the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves image processing and analysis, which could place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image-to-image prediction, which could also place it under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
